body:
You can use the [$group](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/group) stage to aggregate summary
data for groups of one or more documents. MongoDB groups documents based
on the `_id` expression.

> **Note:** You can reference a specific document field by prefixing the field
> name with a `$`.

```javascript
{
  "$group": {
    "_id": <Group By Expression>,
    "<Field Name>": <Aggregation Expression>,
    ...
  }
}
```

> **Example:** The following `$group` stage groups documents by the value of their
> `customerId` field and calculates the number of purchase documents
> that each `customerId` appears in.
>
> ```javascript
> {
>   "$group": {
>     "_id": "$customerId",
>     "numPurchases": { "$sum": 1 }
>   }
> }
> ```
